    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.19.5"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Sigurd Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    College of Notre Dame
                    North Charles St.
                    Baltimore, Maryland
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps"><del/><add>G.</add></hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Next autumn our new library building here at Notre Dame will be dedicated. The English Department of the College is sponsoring an exhibit of Contemporary Poetry as a major attraction. We wonder if you would be willing to donate an autographed copy of a volume of your poetry for that occasion? Failing this, would you care to send us a manuscript copy of a single poem? We shall be deeply grateful for any courtesy you may extend.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Sister Mary Angeline S.S.N.D
                    Head of English Department</signed>
                
                    <dateline>June 6, 1941</dateline>
                </closer>
                
                <note place="left margin">Please mail Washington Post article to Ollie + Enot when you've read it! Dad</note>
                
                <note type="unknown" place="bottom">Dear Ones: A prospect for the East. Also, might contact Dr. <unclear>Rublo</unclear> Walter Brown, Cambridge, Mass., asking for suggestions. Dad</note>              
                
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
